verbose_text: The overexpression of the apolipoprotein family (ApoA1, ApoA2, ApoC3, ApoE) and serum amyloid A protein in comparative proteomic profiles of HCC cases family members have indicated that genetic factors may account for familial aggregation of HCC [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: overexpression of the apolipoprotein family (ApoA1, ApoA2, ApoC3, ApoE) and serum amyloid A protein
